00018 int num_leading_bits(unsigned char n, int bit_val)
00019 {
00020   // 
00021   // Computes the number of leading 0s or 1s (selected by bit_val) in a
00022   // given byte.  For example, the number of leading 0s in 00010110 is
00023   // 3,
00024   // and the number of leading 1s is 0.
00025   // 
00026 
00027   int retval = 0;
00028 
00029   for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
00030     int bit_i = (n >> (7 - i)) & 1;
00031     if (bit_i == bit_val) {
00032       retval++;
00033     } else {
00034       break;
00035     }
00036   }
00037 
00038   return retval;
00039 }

00041 void rle_bits_setup()
00042 {
00043   if(rle_bits_setup_done) {
00044     return;
00045   }
00046 
00047   // 
00048   // Cache the number of leading 0s and 1s for all 8-bit values.
00049   // 
00050   for (int i = 0; i < 256; i++) {
00051     num_leading_0[i] = num_leading_bits(i, 0);
00052     num_leading_1[i] = num_leading_bits(i, 1);
00053   }
00054 
00055   // 
00056   // Cache the bit-strings consisting of all 1s, with lengths from 1 to
00057   // 8.
00058   // 
00059   short o = 0;
00060   for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++) {
00061     ones[i] = o;
00062     o = (o << 1) | 1;
00063   }
00064 }

00066 void rle_put(unsigned char b, rle_state * s, io_buffer * output)
00067 {
00068   int bits = 8;
00069 
00070   while (bits > 0) {
00071     int nr;
00072 
00073     if (s->running_digit == 0) {
00074       nr = num_leading_0[b];
00075     } else {
00076       nr = num_leading_1[b];
00077     }
00078 
00079     if (nr > bits) {
00080       nr = bits;
00081     }
00082 
00083     s->run_length += nr;
00084     bits -= nr;
00085 
00086     if (bits != 0 || (!s->use_extension_word && 
00087                      s->run_length >= s->huffman_length[s->running_digit]-8)) {
00088       b = b << nr;
00089 
00090       if(s->run_length < s->huffman_length[s->running_digit]) {
00091         huffman_put_symbol(&s->huffman[s->running_digit], output, s->run_length);
00092       } else {
00093         huffman_put_symbol(&s->huffman[s->running_digit], output, s->huffman_length[s->running_digit]);
00094         io_buffer_put(output,s->run_length, 24);
00095        
00096       }
00097       s->running_digit = !s->running_digit;
00098       s->run_length = 0;
00099     }

00122
